{"id": "EUVD-2022-1290", "enisaUuid": "35a7fbe3-7693-3788-b6f4-024eb0665a68", "description": "Electron is a framework for writing cross-platform desktop applications using JavaScript, HTML and CSS. A vulnerability in versions prior to `17.0.0-alpha.6`, `16.0.6`, `15.3.5`, `14.2.4`, and `13.6.6` allows renderers to obtain access to a bluetooth device via the web bluetooth API if the app has not configured a custom `select-bluetooth-device` event handler. This has been patched and Electron versions `17.0.0-alpha.6`, `16.0.6`, `15.3.5`, `14.2.4`, and `13.6.6` contain the fix. Code from the GitHub Security Advisory can be added to the app to work around the issue.", "datePublished": "2022-03-22T16:25:12", "dateUpdated": "2025-04-23T18:45:03", "baseScore": 3.4, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:H/UI:R/S:C/C:L/I:N/A:N", "references": ["https://github.com/electron/electron/security/advisories/GHSA-3p22-ghq8-v749", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-21718", "https://github.com/electron/electron/pull/32178", "https://github.com/electron/electron/pull/32240", "https://github.com/electron/electron"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-21718", "GHSA-3p22-ghq8-v749"], "assigner": "GitHub_M", "epss": 1.18, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "11d1943a-c67f-30fc-8888-b97581b0007b", "product": {"name": "electron"}, "product_version": "15.0.0-beta.1, < 15.3.5"}, {"id": "23808539-73b1-3fb5-b1dc-496cad6ad102", "product": {"name": "electron"}, "product_version": "16.0.0-beta.1, < 16.0.6"}, {"id": "6df1abba-2636-330d-bfe9-11380c735c5a", "product": {"name": "electron"}, "product_version": "< 13.6.6"}, {"id": "702ea610-01c9-3e68-9b40-60db214bf06d", "product": {"name": "electron"}, "product_version": "14.0.0-beta.1, < 14.2.4"}, {"id": "73942027-dc1e-380c-b068-df90a2232dab", "product": {"name": "electron"}, "product_version": "17.0.0-alpha.1, \u2264 17.0.0-alpha.5"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "ace4abb4-a228-389c-8430-c0c803580046", "vendor": {"name": "electron"}}], "isEx